Pleased to have joined my fellow colleagues to reaffirm our support for D.C. Statehood. 

DC has a larger population than two states. Yet, these citizens do not have a vote in Congress. Today, the House passed H.R. 51 to end this injustice & bring DC residents one step closer to the representation they deserve. #DCStatehood

node.text:
This week, the House passed H.R. 4, the John R. Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to combat the assault on democracy across America by restoring the power of the Voting Rights Act.
 
The late John Lewis, often referred to as the conscience of the Congress, said the vote is “the most powerful non-violent tool we have in a democracy.” In America, the right to vote must never, ever be compromised. 
 
Congresswoman Terri Sewell’s district is full of history, but she is making progress in addition to honoring that history. Proud to stand with her and House Democrats in fighting #ForThePeople.

Today, I ordered the flags at the U.S Capitol to be flown at half-staff in honor of the U.S. Servicemembers and others killed in the terrorist attack outside of the Kabul airport.

Congress and the Country pray for the innocent lives lost, those injured and the families of all affected.

node.text:
Proud to meet with religious leaders, including Rev. Dr. William J. Barber II and Rev. Dr. Liz Theoharis, co-chairs of the Poor People’s Campaign, yesterday at the Capitol.
 
I came to Congress to ensure no child would ever go to sleep hungry. The Poor People's Campaign is a campaign about the children.
 
Thanks to President Biden, we have a transformative moment For The Children and to #BuildBackBetter for the families of America.

node.text:
Proud to join Dr. Susan Ehrlich, the Initiative for Medicines Access and Knowledge, and Covered California at San Francisco General Hospital yesterday to discuss Democrats’ efforts to lower health care costs #ForThePeople.

Quality, affordable health care must be a right, not a privilege.

node.text:
Proud to join Chairwoman Maxine Waters and American families at Ethel Bradley Early Education Center to discuss how President Biden's #ChildTaxCredit is working #ForThePeople. Today, the next round of checks were sent to families.

The strength of our democracy is a strong working class, middle class and those who aspire to the middle class. Children are America's future. Congressional Democrats are here to protect our democracy and invest in our future.

node.text: Honored to welcome the new Ambassador, Mariangela Zappia of Italy, to the United States at the Capitol this week to discuss COVID-19 response and recovery, advancing international security and stability and addressing the climate crisis. The ties between our two nations are uniquely strong because of our shared priorities and the vital role Italy has played in our history. Today, our Italian American communities continue to offer millions of bridges between our two nations. As the Ambassador Zappia takes on this position, may the strong bonds between the US and Italy continue to grow!
